{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":690,"text":"Chris Anderson: We had Edward Snowden here"},{"time":2860,"text":"a couple days ago,"},{"time":4398,"text":"and this is response time."},{"time":6741,"text":"And several of you have written to me"},{"time":8996,"text":"with questions to ask our guest here from the NSA."},{"time":13639,"text":"So Richard Ledgett is the 15th deputy director"},{"time":15987,"text":"of the National Security Agency,"},{"time":18552,"text":"and he's a senior civilian officer there,"},{"time":21838,"text":"acts as its chief operating officer,"},{"time":23823,"text":"guiding strategies, setting internal policies,"},{"time":27093,"text":"and serving as the principal advisor to the director."},{"time":31473,"text":"And all being well,"},{"time":33349,"text":"welcome, Rick Ledgett, to TED."},{"time":36865,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":43535,"text":"Richard Ledgett: I'm really thankful for the opportunity to talk to folks here."},{"time":47283,"text":"I look forward to the conversation,"},{"time":49237,"text":"so thanks for arranging for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52219,"text":"CA: Thank you, Rick."},{"time":53757,"text":"We appreciate you joining us."},{"time":56324,"text":"It's certainly quite a strong statement"},{"time":58491,"text":"that the NSA is willing to reach out"},{"time":60478,"text":"and show a more open face here."},{"time":64475,"text":"You saw, I think,"},{"time":66428,"text":"the talk and interview that Edward Snowden"},{"time":70321,"text":"gave here a couple days ago."},{"time":71265,"text":"What did you make of it?"},{"time":73704,"text":"RL: So I think it was interesting."},{"time":76855,"text":"We didn't realize that he \nwas going to show up there,"},{"time":79742,"text":"so kudos to you guys for arranging"},{"time":82875,"text":"a nice surprise like that."},{"time":85578,"text":"I think that, like a lot of the things"},{"time":90951,"text":"that have come out since Mr. Snowden"},{"time":95470,"text":"started disclosing classified information,"},{"time":98035,"text":"there were some kernels of truth in there,"},{"time":101501,"text":"but a lot of extrapolations and half-truths in there,"},{"time":104995,"text":"and I'm interested in helping to address those."},{"time":107518,"text":"I think this is a really important conversation"},{"time":109838,"text":"that we're having in the United States"},{"time":111370,"text":"and internationally,"},{"time":112885,"text":"and I think it is important and of import,"},{"time":117294,"text":"and so given that, we need to have that be"},{"time":120754,"text":"a fact-based conversation,"},{"time":122154,"text":"and we want to help make that happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124606,"text":"CA: So the question that a lot \nof people have here is,"},{"time":129223,"text":"what do you make of Snowden's motivations"},{"time":132137,"text":"for doing what he did,"},{"time":134388,"text":"and did he have an alternative\nway that he could have gone?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138878,"text":"RL: He absolutely did"},{"time":141217,"text":"have alternative ways that he could have gone,"},{"time":145415,"text":"and I actually think that characterizing him"},{"time":151009,"text":"as a whistleblower"},{"time":152999,"text":"actually hurts legitimate whistleblowing activities."},{"time":156527,"text":"So what if somebody who works in the NSA --"},{"time":160098,"text":"and there are over 35,000 people who do."},{"time":163102,"text":"They're all great citizens."},{"time":165455,"text":"They're just like your husbands, fathers, sisters,"},{"time":167758,"text":"brothers, neighbors, nephews, friends and relatives,"},{"time":171975,"text":"all of whom are interested in doing the right thing"},{"time":174145,"text":"for their country"},{"time":175332,"text":"and for our allies internationally,"},{"time":178366,"text":"and so there are a variety of venues to address"},{"time":182448,"text":"if folks have a concern."},{"time":183622,"text":"First off, there's their supervisor,"},{"time":185545,"text":"and up through the supervisory chain"},{"time":188237,"text":"within their organization."},{"time":189979,"text":"If folks aren't comfortable with that,"},{"time":191626,"text":"there are a number of inspectors general."},{"time":193981,"text":"In the case of Mr. Snowden, he had the option"},{"time":197522,"text":"of the NSA inspector general,"},{"time":199447,"text":"the Navy inspector general,"},{"time":200767,"text":"the Pacific Command inspector general,"},{"time":202334,"text":"the Department of Defense inspector general,"},{"time":204244,"text":"and the intelligence community inspector general,"},{"time":206350,"text":"any of whom would have both kept\nhis concerns in classified channels"},{"time":210668,"text":"and been happy to address them."},{"time":213299,"text":"(CA and RL speaking at once)"},{"time":215576,"text":"He had the option to go to\ncongressional committees,"},{"time":218179,"text":"and there are mechanisms\nto do that that are in place,"},{"time":221298,"text":"and so he didn't do any of those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223837,"text":"CA: Now, you had said that"},{"time":226827,"text":"Ed Snowden had other avenues"},{"time":229056,"text":"for raising his concerns."},{"time":231751,"text":"The comeback on that is a couple of things:"},{"time":235077,"text":"one, that he certainly believes that as a contractor,"},{"time":238887,"text":"the avenues that would have been available\nto him as an employee weren't available,"},{"time":242648,"text":"two, there's a track record of other whistleblowers,"},{"time":246079,"text":"like [Thomas Andrews Drake] being treated"},{"time":248690,"text":"pretty harshly, by some views,"},{"time":251837,"text":"and thirdly, what he was taking on"},{"time":253490,"text":"was not one specific flaw that he'd discovered,"},{"time":256827,"text":"but programs that had been approved"},{"time":258798,"text":"by all three branches of government."},{"time":261739,"text":"I mean, in that circumstance,"},{"time":264538,"text":"couldn't you argue that what he did"},{"time":266941,"text":"was reasonable?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":269207,"text":"RL: No, I don't agree with that."},{"time":271520,"text":"I think that the —"},{"time":275257,"text":"sorry, I'm getting feedback"},{"time":277392,"text":"through the microphone there —"},{"time":280949,"text":"the actions that he took were inappropriate"},{"time":285776,"text":"because of the fact that \nhe put people's lives at risk,"},{"time":290551,"text":"basically, in the long run,"},{"time":292023,"text":"and I know there's been a lot of talk"},{"time":293587,"text":"in public by Mr. Snowden\nand some of the journalists"},{"time":298251,"text":"that say that the things that have been disclosed"},{"time":301681,"text":"have not put national security and people at risk,"},{"time":305876,"text":"and that is categorically not true."},{"time":310170,"text":"They actually do."},{"time":312077,"text":"I think there's also an amazing arrogance"},{"time":314918,"text":"to the idea that he knows better than"},{"time":319053,"text":"the framers of the Constitution"},{"time":322348,"text":"in how the government should \nbe designed and work"},{"time":324727,"text":"for separation of powers"},{"time":326869,"text":"and the fact that the executive \nand the legislative branch"},{"time":333316,"text":"have to work together and they have\nchecks and balances on each other,"},{"time":335927,"text":"and then the judicial branch,"},{"time":337461,"text":"which oversees the entire process."},{"time":338897,"text":"I think that's extremely arrogant on his part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343118,"text":"CA: Can you give a specific example"},{"time":345424,"text":"of how he put people's lives at risk?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":348880,"text":"RL: Yeah, sure."},{"time":350877,"text":"So the things that he's disclosed,"},{"time":354271,"text":"the capabilities,"},{"time":355786,"text":"and the NSA is a capabilities-based organization,"},{"time":358228,"text":"so when we have foreign intelligence targets,"},{"time":362102,"text":"legitimate things of interest --"},{"time":363733,"text":"like, terrorists is the iconic example,"},{"time":365743,"text":"but it includes things like human traffickers,"},{"time":368837,"text":"drug traffickers,"},{"time":370699,"text":"people who are trying to build\nadvanced weaponry, nuclear weapons,"},{"time":374663,"text":"and build delivery systems for those,"},{"time":376626,"text":"and nation-states who might be executing aggression against their immediate neighbors,"},{"time":380257,"text":"which you may have some visibility"},{"time":382851,"text":"into some of that that's going on right now,"},{"time":385605,"text":"the capabilities are applied"},{"time":389567,"text":"in very discrete and measured and controlled ways."},{"time":394568,"text":"So the unconstrained disclosure \nof those capabilities"},{"time":397356,"text":"means that as adversaries see them"},{"time":399640,"text":"and recognize, \"Hey, I might be vulnerable to this,\""},{"time":402003,"text":"they move away from that,"},{"time":403570,"text":"and we have seen targets in terrorism,"},{"time":406779,"text":"in the nation-state area,"},{"time":408911,"text":"in smugglers of various types, and other folks"},{"time":411913,"text":"who have, because of the disclosures,"},{"time":413866,"text":"moved away from our ability"},{"time":416801,"text":"to have insight into what they're doing."},{"time":418889,"text":"The net effect of that is that our people"},{"time":421853,"text":"who are overseas in dangerous places,"},{"time":423746,"text":"whether they're diplomats or military,"},{"time":425610,"text":"and our allies who are in similar situations,"},{"time":428201,"text":"are at greater risk because we don't see"},{"time":431060,"text":"the threats that are coming their way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434011,"text":"CA: So that's a general response saying that"},{"time":436070,"text":"because of his revelations,"},{"time":438167,"text":"access that you had to certain types of information"},{"time":441033,"text":"has been shut down, has been closed down."},{"time":444604,"text":"But the concern is that the nature of that access"},{"time":448153,"text":"was not necessarily legitimate in the first place."},{"time":451857,"text":"I mean, describe to us this Bullrun program"},{"time":454639,"text":"where it's alleged that the NSA"},{"time":456768,"text":"specifically weakened security"},{"time":459153,"text":"in order to get the type of \naccess that you've spoken of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463722,"text":"RL: So there are, when our"},{"time":468863,"text":"legitimate foreign intelligence targets\nof the type that I described before,"},{"time":471575,"text":"use the global telecommunications system"},{"time":474611,"text":"as their communications methodology,"},{"time":476694,"text":"and they do, because it's a great system,"},{"time":478108,"text":"it's the most complex system ever devised by man,"},{"time":480946,"text":"and it is a wonder,"},{"time":482593,"text":"and lots of folks in the room there"},{"time":484197,"text":"are responsible for the creation"},{"time":486548,"text":"and enhancement of that,"},{"time":487917,"text":"and it's just a wonderful thing."},{"time":490790,"text":"But it's also used by people who are"},{"time":493287,"text":"working against us and our allies."},{"time":495318,"text":"And so if I'm going to pursue them,"},{"time":497749,"text":"I need to have the capability"},{"time":499484,"text":"to go after them,"},{"time":501659,"text":"and again, the controls are in"},{"time":504485,"text":"how I apply that capability,"},{"time":507006,"text":"not that I have the capability itself."},{"time":509252,"text":"Otherwise, if we could make it so that"},{"time":511024,"text":"all the bad guys used one corner of the Internet,"},{"time":513210,"text":"we could have a domain, badguy.com."},{"time":515166,"text":"That would be awesome,"},{"time":516660,"text":"and we could just concentrate all our efforts there."},{"time":518802,"text":"That's not how it works."},{"time":520134,"text":"They're trying to hide"},{"time":522345,"text":"from the government's ability"},{"time":524150,"text":"to isolate and interdict their actions,"},{"time":527433,"text":"and so we have to swim in that same space."},{"time":530245,"text":"But I will tell you this."},{"time":531847,"text":"So NSA has two missions."},{"time":533326,"text":"One is the Signals Intelligence mission"},{"time":534776,"text":"that we've unfortunately read so\nmuch about in the press."},{"time":538403,"text":"The other one is the Information Assurance mission,"},{"time":540141,"text":"which is to protect the national security\nsystems of the United States,"},{"time":543052,"text":"and by that, that's things like"},{"time":545020,"text":"the communications that the president uses,"},{"time":547036,"text":"the communications that\ncontrol our nuclear weapons,"},{"time":549641,"text":"the communications that our\nmilitary uses around the world,"},{"time":551910,"text":"and the communications that we use with our allies,"},{"time":554401,"text":"and that some of our allies themselves use."},{"time":556125,"text":"And so we make recommendations\non standards to use,"},{"time":561962,"text":"and we use those same standards,"},{"time":563789,"text":"and so we are invested"},{"time":565667,"text":"in making sure that those communications"},{"time":567912,"text":"are secure for their intended purposes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571525,"text":"CA: But it sounds like what you're saying is that"},{"time":573474,"text":"when it comes to the Internet at large,"},{"time":577219,"text":"any strategy is fair game"},{"time":579846,"text":"if it improves America's safety."},{"time":582762,"text":"And I think this is partly where there is such"},{"time":584820,"text":"a divide of opinion,"},{"time":586205,"text":"that there's a lot of people in this room"},{"time":587455,"text":"and around the world"},{"time":588828,"text":"who think very differently about the Internet."},{"time":590478,"text":"They think of it as a momentous"},{"time":593465,"text":"invention of humanity,"},{"time":595063,"text":"kind of on a par with the\nGutenberg press, for example."},{"time":598227,"text":"It's the bringer of knowledge to all."},{"time":600682,"text":"It's the connector of all."},{"time":602386,"text":"And it's viewed in those sort of idealistic terms."},{"time":605771,"text":"And from that lens,"},{"time":607344,"text":"what the NSA has done is equivalent to"},{"time":609941,"text":"the authorities back in Germany"},{"time":612101,"text":"inserting some device into every printing press"},{"time":614970,"text":"that would reveal which books people bought"},{"time":618511,"text":"and what they read."},{"time":620531,"text":"Can you understand that from that viewpoint,"},{"time":622762,"text":"it feels outrageous?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":626967,"text":"RL: I do understand that, and I actually share\nthe view of the utility of the Internet,"},{"time":630269,"text":"and I would argue it's bigger than the Internet."},{"time":631971,"text":"It is a global telecommunications system."},{"time":634382,"text":"The Internet is a big chunk of \nthat, but there is a lot more."},{"time":636833,"text":"And I think that people have legitimate concerns"},{"time":640176,"text":"about the balance between\ntransparency and secrecy."},{"time":646482,"text":"That's sort of been couched as a balance"},{"time":648422,"text":"between privacy and national security."},{"time":652058,"text":"I don't think that's the right framing."},{"time":653478,"text":"I think it really is transparency and secrecy."},{"time":655843,"text":"And so that's the national and international conversation that we're having,"},{"time":659402,"text":"and we want to participate in that, and want"},{"time":660801,"text":"people to participate in it in an informed way."},{"time":663241,"text":"So there are things,"},{"time":665152,"text":"let me talk there a little bit more,"},{"time":666602,"text":"there are things that we need\nto be transparent about:"},{"time":670371,"text":"our authorities, our processes,"},{"time":672398,"text":"our oversight, who we are."},{"time":674452,"text":"We, NSA, have not done a good job of that,"},{"time":676218,"text":"and I think that's part of the reason"},{"time":677606,"text":"that this has been so revelational"},{"time":680335,"text":"and so sensational in the media."},{"time":682531,"text":"Nobody knew who we were. We were the No Such Agency, the Never Say Anything."},{"time":686657,"text":"There's takeoffs of our logo"},{"time":689306,"text":"of an eagle with headphones on around it."},{"time":692325,"text":"And so that's the public characterization."},{"time":695948,"text":"And so we need to be more\ntransparent about those things."},{"time":700284,"text":"What we don't need to be transparent about,"},{"time":701702,"text":"because it's bad for the U.S.,"},{"time":704040,"text":"it's bad for all those other\ncountries that we work with"},{"time":706623,"text":"and that we help provide information"},{"time":708716,"text":"that helps them secure themselves"},{"time":710438,"text":"and their people,"},{"time":711947,"text":"it's bad to expose operations and capabilities"},{"time":715837,"text":"in a way that allows the people\nthat we're all working against,"},{"time":721129,"text":"the generally recognized bad guys,"},{"time":726092,"text":"to counter those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728392,"text":"CA: But isn't it also bad to deal"},{"time":731417,"text":"a kind of body blow to the American companies"},{"time":734821,"text":"that have essentially given the world"},{"time":736717,"text":"most of the Internet services that matter?"},{"time":741897,"text":"RL: It is. It's really the companies are"},{"time":745289,"text":"in a tough position, as are we,"},{"time":748677,"text":"because the companies,"},{"time":750618,"text":"we compel them to provide information,"},{"time":752950,"text":"just like every other nation in the world does."},{"time":754933,"text":"Every industrialized nation in the world"},{"time":758207,"text":"has a lawful intercept program"},{"time":760307,"text":"where they are requiring companies"},{"time":762805,"text":"to provide them with information"},{"time":764216,"text":"that they need for their security,"},{"time":765871,"text":"and the companies that are involved"},{"time":768098,"text":"have complied with those programs"},{"time":769526,"text":"in the same way that they have to do"},{"time":771144,"text":"when they're operating in Russia or the U.K."},{"time":774594,"text":"or China or India or France,"},{"time":778880,"text":"any country that you choose to name."},{"time":780898,"text":"And so the fact that these revelations"},{"time":785807,"text":"have been broadly characterized as"},{"time":788101,"text":"\"you can't trust company A because"},{"time":789991,"text":"your privacy is suspect with them\""},{"time":793506,"text":"is actually only accurate in the sense that"},{"time":797547,"text":"it's accurate with every other company in the world"},{"time":800283,"text":"that deals with any of those countries in the world."},{"time":802442,"text":"And so it's being picked up by people"},{"time":804570,"text":"as a marketing advantage,"},{"time":806164,"text":"and it's being marketed that \nway by several countries,"},{"time":807937,"text":"including some of our allied countries,"},{"time":809448,"text":"where they are saying,"},{"time":810950,"text":"\"Hey, you can't trust the U.S.,"},{"time":812479,"text":"but you can trust our telecom company,"},{"time":815065,"text":"because we're safe.\""},{"time":816419,"text":"And they're actually using that to counter"},{"time":818078,"text":"the very large technological edge"},{"time":820396,"text":"that U.S. companies have"},{"time":822205,"text":"in areas like the cloud and\nInternet-based technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826111,"text":"CA: You're sitting there with the American flag,"},{"time":829118,"text":"and the American Constitution guarantees"},{"time":832688,"text":"freedom from unreasonable search and seizure."},{"time":835535,"text":"How do you characterize"},{"time":837496,"text":"the American citizen's right to privacy?"},{"time":841976,"text":"Is there such a right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":844257,"text":"RL: Yeah, of course there is."},{"time":846993,"text":"And we devote an inordinate\namount of time and pressure,"},{"time":850036,"text":"inordinate and appropriate, actually I should say,"},{"time":852320,"text":"amount of time and effort in order to ensure"},{"time":854528,"text":"that we protect that privacy."},{"time":856860,"text":"and beyond that, the privacy of citizens"},{"time":859917,"text":"around the world, it's not just Americans."},{"time":863566,"text":"Several things come into play here."},{"time":865466,"text":"First, we're all in the same network."},{"time":867214,"text":"My communications,"},{"time":868788,"text":"I'm a user of a particular Internet email service"},{"time":872935,"text":"that is the number one email service of choice"},{"time":876906,"text":"by terrorists around the world, number one."},{"time":878499,"text":"So I'm there right beside them in email space"},{"time":881224,"text":"in the Internet."},{"time":883113,"text":"And so we need to be able to pick that apart"},{"time":886705,"text":"and find the information that's relevant."},{"time":893131,"text":"In doing so, we're going to necessarily encounter"},{"time":896493,"text":"Americans and innocent foreign citizens"},{"time":898561,"text":"who are just going about their business,"},{"time":900107,"text":"and so we have procedures in\nplace that shreds that out,"},{"time":902805,"text":"that says, when you find that,"},{"time":905020,"text":"not if you find it, when you find it,\nbecause you're certain to find it,"},{"time":907287,"text":"here's how you protect that."},{"time":909070,"text":"These are called minimization procedures."},{"time":911175,"text":"They're approved by the attorney general"},{"time":913203,"text":"and constitutionally based."},{"time":914803,"text":"And so we protect those."},{"time":917283,"text":"And then, for people, citizens of the world"},{"time":921754,"text":"who are going about their lawful business"},{"time":923633,"text":"on a day-to-day basis,"},{"time":925340,"text":"the president on his January 17 speech,"},{"time":927636,"text":"laid out some additional protections"},{"time":929129,"text":"that we are providing to them."},{"time":931188,"text":"So I think absolutely,"},{"time":933060,"text":"folks do have a right to privacy,"},{"time":934595,"text":"and that we work very hard to make sure"},{"time":937214,"text":"that that right to privacy is protected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940020,"text":"CA: What about foreigners using"},{"time":941756,"text":"American companies' Internet services?"},{"time":943906,"text":"Do they have any privacy rights?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":947751,"text":"RL: They do. They do, in the sense of,"},{"time":950424,"text":"the only way that we are able to compel"},{"time":956164,"text":"one of those companies to provide us information"},{"time":958490,"text":"is when it falls into one of three categories:"},{"time":961952,"text":"We can identify that this particular person,"},{"time":965504,"text":"identified by a selector of some kind,"},{"time":967894,"text":"is associated with counterterrorist"},{"time":971250,"text":"or proliferation or other foreign intelligence target."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976499,"text":"CA: Much has been made of the fact that"},{"time":978281,"text":"a lot of the information that you've obtained"},{"time":980747,"text":"through these programs is essentially metadata."},{"time":983023,"text":"It's not necessarily the actual words"},{"time":985318,"text":"that someone has written in an email"},{"time":986971,"text":"or given on a phone call."},{"time":988320,"text":"It's who they wrote to and when, and so forth."},{"time":992369,"text":"But it's been argued,"},{"time":993905,"text":"and someone here in the audience has talked"},{"time":996016,"text":"to a former NSA analyst who said"},{"time":998483,"text":"metadata is actually much more invasive"},{"time":1000870,"text":"than the core data,"},{"time":1002273,"text":"because in the core data"},{"time":1003406,"text":"you present yourself as you want to be presented."},{"time":1006633,"text":"With metadata, who knows what the conclusions are"},{"time":1009339,"text":"that are drawn?"},{"time":1010755,"text":"Is there anything to that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012761,"text":"RL: I don't really understand that argument."},{"time":1014550,"text":"I think that metadata's important\nfor a couple of reasons."},{"time":1017450,"text":"Metadata is the information that lets you"},{"time":1021928,"text":"find connections that people are trying to hide."},{"time":1025319,"text":"So when a terrorist is corresponding"},{"time":1027330,"text":"with somebody else who's not known to us"},{"time":1029175,"text":"but is engaged in doing or\nsupporting terrorist activity,"},{"time":1031783,"text":"or someone who's violating international sanctions"},{"time":1034209,"text":"by providing nuclear weapons-related material"},{"time":1037286,"text":"to a country like Iran or North Korea,"},{"time":1039612,"text":"is trying to hide that activity\nbecause it's illicit activity."},{"time":1043189,"text":"What metadata lets you do is connect that."},{"time":1045999,"text":"The alternative to that"},{"time":1047531,"text":"is one that's much less efficient"},{"time":1049150,"text":"and much more invasive of privacy,"},{"time":1050531,"text":"which is gigantic amounts of content collection."},{"time":1054367,"text":"So metadata, in that sense,"},{"time":1055760,"text":"actually is privacy-enhancing."},{"time":1058156,"text":"And we don't, contrary to some of the stuff"},{"time":1060261,"text":"that's been printed,"},{"time":1061976,"text":"we don't sit there and grind out"},{"time":1064745,"text":"metadata profiles of average people."},{"time":1067582,"text":"If you're not connected"},{"time":1069538,"text":"to one of those valid intelligence targets,"},{"time":1072590,"text":"you are not of interest to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076003,"text":"CA: So in terms of the threats"},{"time":1079175,"text":"that face America overall,"},{"time":1081487,"text":"where would you place terrorism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1084699,"text":"RL: I think terrorism is still number one."},{"time":1087797,"text":"I think that we have never been in a time"},{"time":1091701,"text":"where there are more places"},{"time":1093692,"text":"where things are going badly"},{"time":1096545,"text":"and forming the petri dish in which terrorists"},{"time":1100446,"text":"take advantage of the lack of governance."},{"time":1105756,"text":"An old boss of mine, Tom Fargo, Admiral Fargo,"},{"time":1109393,"text":"used to describe it as arcs of instability."},{"time":1111606,"text":"And so you have a lot of those arcs of instability"},{"time":1113974,"text":"in the world right now,"},{"time":1115667,"text":"in places like Syria, where there's a civil war"},{"time":1117504,"text":"going on and you have massive numbers,"},{"time":1120214,"text":"thousands and thousands of foreign fighters"},{"time":1121949,"text":"who are coming into Syria"},{"time":1123682,"text":"to learn how to be terrorists"},{"time":1125185,"text":"and practice that activity,"},{"time":1127286,"text":"and lots of those people are Westerners"},{"time":1129985,"text":"who hold passports to European countries"},{"time":1133714,"text":"or in some cases the United States,"},{"time":1135466,"text":"and so they are basically learning how"},{"time":1137867,"text":"to do jihad and have expressed intent"},{"time":1141347,"text":"to go out and do that later on"},{"time":1143760,"text":"in their home countries."},{"time":1145427,"text":"You've got places like Iraq,"},{"time":1146748,"text":"which is suffering from a high\nlevel of sectarian violence,"},{"time":1149530,"text":"again a breeding ground for terrorism."},{"time":1152181,"text":"And you have the activity in the Horn of Africa"},{"time":1154687,"text":"and the Sahel area of Africa."},{"time":1157734,"text":"Again, lots of weak governance"},{"time":1160262,"text":"which forms a breeding ground for terrorist activity."},{"time":1164153,"text":"So I think it's very serious. I think it's number one."},{"time":1166147,"text":"I think number two is cyber threat."},{"time":1168401,"text":"I think cyber is a threat in three ways:"},{"time":1174165,"text":"One way, and probably the most common way"},{"time":1177919,"text":"that people have heard about it,"},{"time":1180111,"text":"is due to the theft of intellectual property,"},{"time":1182111,"text":"so basically, foreign countries going in,"},{"time":1186415,"text":"stealing companies' secrets,"},{"time":1188292,"text":"and then providing that information"},{"time":1190290,"text":"to state-owned enterprises"},{"time":1192027,"text":"or companies connected to the government"},{"time":1194976,"text":"to help them leapfrog technology"},{"time":1197479,"text":"or to gain business intelligence"},{"time":1199554,"text":"that's then used to win contracts overseas."},{"time":1202222,"text":"That is a hugely costly set of\nactivities that's going on right now."},{"time":1205961,"text":"Several nation-states are doing it."},{"time":1207428,"text":"Second is the denial-of-service attacks."},{"time":1210653,"text":"You're probably aware that there have been"},{"time":1212032,"text":"a spate of those directed against"},{"time":1214003,"text":"the U.S. financial sector since 2012."},{"time":1217591,"text":"Again, that's a nation-state who\nis executing those attacks,"},{"time":1220208,"text":"and they're doing that"},{"time":1221281,"text":"as a semi-anonymous way of reprisal."},{"time":1226034,"text":"And the last one is destructive attacks,"},{"time":1227424,"text":"and those are the ones that concern me the most."},{"time":1228950,"text":"Those are on the rise."},{"time":1230350,"text":"You have the attack against Saudi Aramco in 2012,"},{"time":1233980,"text":"August of 2012."},{"time":1235670,"text":"It took down about 35,000 of their computers"},{"time":1237955,"text":"with a Wiper-style virus."},{"time":1239747,"text":"You had a follow-on a week later"},{"time":1241660,"text":"to a Qatari company."},{"time":1243194,"text":"You had March of 2013,"},{"time":1245335,"text":"you had a South Korean attack"},{"time":1248006,"text":"that was attributed in the press to North Korea"},{"time":1250439,"text":"that took out thousands of computers."},{"time":1252494,"text":"Those are on the rise,"},{"time":1253939,"text":"and we see people expressing interest"},{"time":1256673,"text":"in those capabilities"},{"time":1257849,"text":"and a desire to employ them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1259866,"text":"CA: Okay, so a couple of things here,"},{"time":1261432,"text":"because this is really the core of this, almost."},{"time":1263374,"text":"I mean, first of all,"},{"time":1264638,"text":"a lot of people who look at risk"},{"time":1266196,"text":"and look at the numbers"},{"time":1267413,"text":"don't understand this belief that terrorism"},{"time":1269673,"text":"is still the number one threat."},{"time":1271557,"text":"Apart from September 11,"},{"time":1273185,"text":"I think the numbers are that\nin the last 30 or 40 years"},{"time":1275540,"text":"about 500 Americans have died from terrorism,"},{"time":1278641,"text":"mostly from homegrown terrorists."},{"time":1282624,"text":"The chance in the last few years"},{"time":1284211,"text":"of being killed by terrorism"},{"time":1285934,"text":"is far less than the chance\nof being killed by lightning."},{"time":1289918,"text":"I guess you would say that a single nuclear incident"},{"time":1293324,"text":"or bioterrorism act or something like that"},{"time":1296650,"text":"would change those numbers."},{"time":1298551,"text":"Would that be the point of view?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1300713,"text":"RL: Well, I'd say two things."},{"time":1301889,"text":"One is, the reason that there hasn't been"},{"time":1303815,"text":"a major attack in the United States since 9/11,"},{"time":1305625,"text":"that is not an accident."},{"time":1307181,"text":"That's a lot of hard work that we have done,"},{"time":1309367,"text":"that other folks"},{"time":1310748,"text":"in the intelligence community have done,"},{"time":1312131,"text":"that the military has done,"},{"time":1313312,"text":"and that our allies around the globe have done."},{"time":1315360,"text":"You've heard the numbers about"},{"time":1317811,"text":"the tip of the iceberg in terms"},{"time":1320343,"text":"of numbers of terrorist attacks that NSA programs"},{"time":1322913,"text":"contributed to stopping was 54,"},{"time":1325672,"text":"25 of those in Europe,"},{"time":1327494,"text":"and of those 25,"},{"time":1329624,"text":"18 of them occurred in three countries,"},{"time":1332229,"text":"some of which are our allies,"},{"time":1334092,"text":"and some of which are beating the heck out of us"},{"time":1336291,"text":"over the NSA programs, by the way."},{"time":1340768,"text":"So that's not an accident that those things happen."},{"time":1343460,"text":"That's hard work. That's us finding intelligence"},{"time":1345785,"text":"on terrorist activities"},{"time":1347615,"text":"and interdicting them through one way or another,"},{"time":1349189,"text":"through law enforcement,"},{"time":1350520,"text":"through cooperative activities with other countries"},{"time":1353350,"text":"and sometimes through military action."},{"time":1356466,"text":"The other thing I would say is that"},{"time":1359359,"text":"your idea of nuclear or chem-bio-threat"},{"time":1364625,"text":"is not at all far-fetched"},{"time":1366141,"text":"and in fact there are a number of groups"},{"time":1367879,"text":"who have for several years expressed interest"},{"time":1369766,"text":"and desire in obtaining those capabilities"},{"time":1372306,"text":"and work towards that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1374066,"text":"CA: It's also been said that,"},{"time":1375642,"text":"of those 54 alleged incidents,"},{"time":1378342,"text":"that as few as zero of them"},{"time":1380190,"text":"were actually anything to do"},{"time":1381252,"text":"with these controversial programs"},{"time":1383099,"text":"that Mr. Snowden revealed,"},{"time":1386831,"text":"that it was basically through\nother forms of intelligence,"},{"time":1390748,"text":"that you're looking for a needle in a haystack,"},{"time":1393638,"text":"and the effects of these programs,"},{"time":1395200,"text":"these controversial programs,"},{"time":1396231,"text":"is just to add hay to the stack,"},{"time":1398303,"text":"not to really find the needle."},{"time":1399883,"text":"The needle was found by other methods."},{"time":1401965,"text":"Isn't there something to that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1406089,"text":"RL: No, there's actually two programs"},{"time":1408497,"text":"that are typically implicated in that discussion."},{"time":1410914,"text":"One is the section 215 program,"},{"time":1413392,"text":"the U.S. telephony metadata program,"},{"time":1416370,"text":"and the other one is"},{"time":1418410,"text":"popularly called the PRISM program,"},{"time":1420004,"text":"and it's actually section 702 \nof the FISA Amendment Act."},{"time":1423252,"text":"But the 215 program"},{"time":1427442,"text":"is only relevant to threats"},{"time":1429169,"text":"that are directed against the United States,"},{"time":1431428,"text":"and there have been a dozen threats"},{"time":1434328,"text":"where that was implicated."},{"time":1435643,"text":"Now what you'll see people say publicly"},{"time":1438832,"text":"is there is no \"but for\" case,"},{"time":1440868,"text":"and so there is no case where, but for that,"},{"time":1444681,"text":"the threat would have happened."},{"time":1446382,"text":"But that actually indicates a lack of understanding"},{"time":1450589,"text":"of how terrorist investigations actually work."},{"time":1455706,"text":"You think about on television,"},{"time":1457184,"text":"you watch a murder mystery."},{"time":1458516,"text":"What do you start with? You start with a body,"},{"time":1460046,"text":"and then they work their way\nfrom there to solve the crime."},{"time":1462282,"text":"We're actually starting well before that,"},{"time":1463813,"text":"hopefully before there are any bodies,"},{"time":1465314,"text":"and we're trying to build the case for"},{"time":1467747,"text":"who the people are, what they're trying to do,"},{"time":1470177,"text":"and that involves massive amounts of information."},{"time":1473027,"text":"Think of it is as mosaic,"},{"time":1474508,"text":"and it's hard to say that any one piece of a mosaic"},{"time":1476670,"text":"was necessary to building the mosaic,"},{"time":1479302,"text":"but to build the complete picture,"},{"time":1481031,"text":"you need to have all the pieces of information."},{"time":1482996,"text":"On the other, the non-U.S.-related\nthreats out of those 54,"},{"time":1486101,"text":"the other 42 of them,"},{"time":1489290,"text":"the PRISM program was hugely relevant to that,"},{"time":1493920,"text":"and in fact was material in contributing"},{"time":1496906,"text":"to stopping those attacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1498788,"text":"CA: Snowden said two days ago"},{"time":1500125,"text":"that terrorism has always been"},{"time":1503495,"text":"what is called in the intelligence world"},{"time":1505623,"text":"\"a cover for action,\""},{"time":1507169,"text":"that it's something that,"},{"time":1509106,"text":"because it invokes such a powerful"},{"time":1510822,"text":"emotional response in people,"},{"time":1512661,"text":"it allows the initiation of these programs"},{"time":1515295,"text":"to achieve powers that an organization like yours"},{"time":1518856,"text":"couldn't otherwise have."},{"time":1520423,"text":"Is there any internal debate about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1523875,"text":"RL: Yeah."},{"time":1525287,"text":"I mean, we debate these things all the time,"},{"time":1527287,"text":"and there is discussion that goes on"},{"time":1530046,"text":"in the executive branch"},{"time":1531967,"text":"and within NSA itself"},{"time":1534030,"text":"and the intelligence community about"},{"time":1535685,"text":"what's right, what's proportionate,"},{"time":1537045,"text":"what's the correct thing to do."},{"time":1538306,"text":"And it's important to note that the programs"},{"time":1539884,"text":"that we're talking about"},{"time":1541231,"text":"were all authorized by two different presidents,"},{"time":1544633,"text":"two different political parties,"},{"time":1546378,"text":"by Congress twice,"},{"time":1548513,"text":"and by federal judges 16 different times,"},{"time":1552349,"text":"and so this is not NSA running off"},{"time":1557061,"text":"and doing its own thing."},{"time":1558524,"text":"This is a legitimate activity"},{"time":1560972,"text":"of the United States foreign government"},{"time":1563490,"text":"that was agreed to by all the branches"},{"time":1565665,"text":"of the United States government,"},{"time":1567649,"text":"and President Madison would have been proud."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1570698,"text":"CA: And yet, when congressmen discovered"},{"time":1574787,"text":"what was actually being done \nwith that authorization,"},{"time":1577017,"text":"many of them were completely shocked."},{"time":1579886,"text":"Or do you think that is not a legitimate reaction,"},{"time":1583232,"text":"that it's only because it's now come out publicly,"},{"time":1585337,"text":"that they really knew exactly what you were doing"},{"time":1588439,"text":"with the powers they had granted you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1590775,"text":"RL: Congress is a big body."},{"time":1592449,"text":"There's 535 of them,"},{"time":1594426,"text":"and they change out frequently,"},{"time":1596567,"text":"in the case of the House, every two years,"},{"time":1598425,"text":"and I think that the NSA provided"},{"time":1602201,"text":"all the relevant information\nto our oversight committees,"},{"time":1605338,"text":"and then the dissemination of that information"},{"time":1607616,"text":"by the oversight committees throughout Congress"},{"time":1609515,"text":"is something that they manage."},{"time":1612149,"text":"I think I would say that Congress members"},{"time":1617005,"text":"had the opportunity to make themselves aware,"},{"time":1620836,"text":"and in fact a significant number of them,"},{"time":1622705,"text":"the ones who are assigned oversight responsibility,"},{"time":1626163,"text":"did have the ability to do that."},{"time":1627337,"text":"And you've actually had the chairs of\nthose committees say that in public."},{"time":1631275,"text":"CA: Now, you mentioned the \nthreat of cyberattacks,"},{"time":1632832,"text":"and I don't think anyone in this room would disagree"},{"time":1634999,"text":"that that is a huge concern,"},{"time":1636889,"text":"but do you accept that there's a tradeoff"},{"time":1638723,"text":"between offensive and defensive strategies,"},{"time":1641134,"text":"and that it's possible that the very measures taken"},{"time":1643959,"text":"to, \"weaken encryption,\""},{"time":1646628,"text":"and allow yourself to find the bad guys,"},{"time":1648781,"text":"might also open the door to forms of cyberattack?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1653054,"text":"RL: So I think two things."},{"time":1655897,"text":"One is, you said weaken encryption. I didn't."},{"time":1659744,"text":"And the other one is that"},{"time":1664870,"text":"the NSA has both of those missions,"},{"time":1667646,"text":"and we are heavily biased towards defense,"},{"time":1669927,"text":"and, actually, the vulnerabilities that we find"},{"time":1673444,"text":"in the overwhelming majority of cases,"},{"time":1675545,"text":"we disclose to the people who are responsible"},{"time":1678318,"text":"for manufacturing or developing those products."},{"time":1681681,"text":"We have a great track record of that,"},{"time":1683064,"text":"and we're actually working on a proposal right now"},{"time":1685050,"text":"to be transparent and to\npublish transparency reports"},{"time":1688220,"text":"in the same way that the Internet companies"},{"time":1691106,"text":"are being allowed to publish\ntransparency reports for them."},{"time":1694973,"text":"We want to be more transparent about that."},{"time":1696971,"text":"So again, we eat our own dog food."},{"time":1700100,"text":"We use the standards, we use the products"},{"time":1702353,"text":"that we recommend,"},{"time":1705008,"text":"and so it's in our interest"},{"time":1707303,"text":"to keep our communications protected"},{"time":1709941,"text":"in the same way that other people's need to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1713745,"text":"CA: Edward Snowden,"},{"time":1716935,"text":"when, after his talk, was wandering the halls here"},{"time":1721363,"text":"in the bot,"},{"time":1722608,"text":"and I heard him say to a couple of people,"},{"time":1724796,"text":"they asked him about what he thought"},{"time":1726413,"text":"of the NSA overall,"},{"time":1728006,"text":"and he was very complimentary about the people"},{"time":1730779,"text":"who work with you,"},{"time":1732800,"text":"said that it's a really"},{"time":1736723,"text":"impassioned group of employees"},{"time":1738683,"text":"who are seeking to do the right thing,"},{"time":1741132,"text":"and that the problems have come from"},{"time":1744086,"text":"just some badly conceived policies."},{"time":1747205,"text":"He came over certainly very reasonably and calmly."},{"time":1751650,"text":"He didn't come over like a crazy man."},{"time":1753825,"text":"Would you accept that at least,"},{"time":1755795,"text":"even if you disagree with how he did it,"},{"time":1758811,"text":"that he has opened a debate that matters?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1762835,"text":"RL: So I think that the discussion"},{"time":1765233,"text":"is an important one to have."},{"time":1767097,"text":"I do not like the way that he did it."},{"time":1770473,"text":"I think there were a number of other ways"},{"time":1772478,"text":"that he could have done that"},{"time":1773940,"text":"that would have not endangered our people"},{"time":1777236,"text":"and the people of other nations"},{"time":1779884,"text":"through losing visibility"},{"time":1781995,"text":"into what our adversaries are doing."},{"time":1784726,"text":"But I do think it's an important conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1787412,"text":"CA: It's been reported that there's"},{"time":1788951,"text":"almost a difference of opinion"},{"time":1791060,"text":"with you and your colleagues"},{"time":1792531,"text":"over any scenario in which"},{"time":1794584,"text":"he might be offered an amnesty deal."},{"time":1797187,"text":"I think your boss, General Keith Alexander,"},{"time":1799898,"text":"has said that that would be a terrible example"},{"time":1801884,"text":"for others;"},{"time":1803349,"text":"you can't negotiate with someone"},{"time":1805006,"text":"who's broken the law in that way."},{"time":1807014,"text":"But you've been quoted as saying that,"},{"time":1809023,"text":"if Snowden could prove that he was surrendering"},{"time":1812231,"text":"all undisclosed documents,"},{"time":1814027,"text":"that a deal maybe should be considered."},{"time":1816266,"text":"Do you still think that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1819236,"text":"RL: Yeah, so actually,"},{"time":1820754,"text":"this is my favorite thing about\nthat \"60 Minutes\" interview"},{"time":1823337,"text":"was all the misquotes that came from that."},{"time":1825049,"text":"What I actually said, in \nresponse to a question about,"},{"time":1827964,"text":"would you entertain any discussions"},{"time":1829776,"text":"of mitigating action against Snowden,"},{"time":1836161,"text":"I said, yeah, it's worth a conversation."},{"time":1837993,"text":"This is something that the attorney general"},{"time":1839628,"text":"of the United States and the president also"},{"time":1841558,"text":"actually have both talked about this,"},{"time":1843096,"text":"and I defer to the attorney general,"},{"time":1844465,"text":"because this is his lane."},{"time":1846012,"text":"But there is a strong tradition"},{"time":1848521,"text":"in American jurisprudence"},{"time":1851713,"text":"of having discussions with people"},{"time":1856288,"text":"who have been charged with crimes in order to,"},{"time":1858132,"text":"if it benefits the government,"},{"time":1859648,"text":"to get something out of that,"},{"time":1862026,"text":"that there's always room for that kind of discussion."},{"time":1864660,"text":"So I'm not presupposing any outcome,"},{"time":1866349,"text":"but there is always room for discussion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1870085,"text":"CA: To a lay person it seems like"},{"time":1871685,"text":"he has certain things to offer the U.S.,"},{"time":1875053,"text":"the government, you, others,"},{"time":1876792,"text":"in terms of putting things right"},{"time":1878473,"text":"and helping figure out a smarter policy,"},{"time":1880531,"text":"a smarter way forward for the future."},{"time":1886988,"text":"Do you see, has that kind of possibility"},{"time":1889061,"text":"been entertained at all?"},{"time":1891459,"text":"RL: So that's out of my lane."},{"time":1893097,"text":"That's not an NSA thing."},{"time":1894626,"text":"That would be a Department of Justice"},{"time":1896833,"text":"sort of discussion."},{"time":1899330,"text":"I'll defer to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1902626,"text":"CA: Rick, when Ed Snowden ended his talk,"},{"time":1905591,"text":"I offered him the chance to\nshare an idea worth spreading."},{"time":1909336,"text":"What would be your idea worth spreading"},{"time":1910989,"text":"for this group?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1913271,"text":"RL: So I think, learn the facts."},{"time":1915263,"text":"This is a really important conversation,"},{"time":1917879,"text":"and it impacts, it's not just NSA,"},{"time":1919955,"text":"it's not just the government,"},{"time":1921153,"text":"it's you, it's the Internet companies."},{"time":1924061,"text":"The issue of privacy and personal data"},{"time":1927179,"text":"is much bigger than just the government,"},{"time":1928756,"text":"and so learn the facts."},{"time":1930667,"text":"Don't rely on headlines,"},{"time":1932263,"text":"don't rely on sound bites,"},{"time":1933939,"text":"don't rely on one-sided conversations."},{"time":1936419,"text":"So that's the idea, I think, worth spreading."},{"time":1939568,"text":"We have a sign, a badge tab,"},{"time":1942961,"text":"we wear badges at work with lanyards,"},{"time":1944850,"text":"and if I could make a plug,"},{"time":1946263,"text":"my badge lanyard at work says, \"Dallas Cowboys.\""},{"time":1949010,"text":"Go Dallas."},{"time":1952507,"text":"I've just alienated half the audience, I know."},{"time":1955173,"text":"So the lanyard that our people"},{"time":1959069,"text":"who work in the organization"},{"time":1960854,"text":"that does our crypto-analytic work"},{"time":1963274,"text":"have a tab that says, \"Look at the data.\""},{"time":1965215,"text":"So that's the idea worth spreading."},{"time":1966751,"text":"Look at the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1969000,"text":"CA: Rick, it took a certain amount of courage,"},{"time":1971992,"text":"I think, actually, to come and speak openly"},{"time":1974607,"text":"to this group."},{"time":1975861,"text":"It's not something the NSA\nhas done a lot of in the past,"},{"time":1978528,"text":"and plus the technology has been challenging."},{"time":1981623,"text":"We truly appreciate you doing that"},{"time":1983404,"text":"and sharing in this very important conversation."},{"time":1985817,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1987958,"text":"RL: Thanks, Chris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1989897,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}